        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/wwilson/{size}/88_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-05-13T04:07:13.680Z",
        "cooked": "<p>A cautionary note: all the fault-tolerance in the world won\u2019t help you if your database grows a dependency on an external system (DNS) that can be down or otherwise unreachable.</p>\n<p>I\u2019m not saying it\u2019s always a bad idea, but think carefully about what kind of SLO you\u2019re aiming for, and how deliberately coupling things such that a failure in an unrelated system can bring FDB down could impact that.</p>",
